{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"As other speakers have said, it's a rather daunting experience --"},{"time":2000,"text":"a particularly daunting experience -- to be speaking in front of this audience."},{"time":5000,"text":"But unlike the other speakers, I'm not going to tell you about"},{"time":8000,"text":"the mysteries of the universe, or the wonders of evolution,"},{"time":10000,"text":"or the really clever, innovative ways people are attacking"},{"time":14000,"text":"the major inequalities in our world."},{"time":16000,"text":"Or even the challenges of nation-states in the modern global economy."},{"time":21000,"text":"My brief, as you've just heard, is to tell you about statistics --"},{"time":25000,"text":"and, to be more precise, to tell you some exciting things about statistics."},{"time":28000,"text":"And that's --"},{"time":29000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":30000,"text":"-- that's rather more challenging"},{"time":32000,"text":"than all the speakers before me and all the ones coming after me."},{"time":34000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":36000,"text":"One of my senior colleagues told me, when I was a youngster in this profession,"},{"time":41000,"text":"rather proudly, that statisticians were people who liked figures"},{"time":45000,"text":"but didn't have the personality skills to become accountants."},{"time":48000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":50000,"text":"And there's another in-joke among statisticians, and that's,"},{"time":53000,"text":"\"How do you tell the introverted statistician from the extroverted statistician?\""},{"time":56000,"text":"To which the answer is,"},{"time":58000,"text":"\"The extroverted statistician's the one who looks at the other person's shoes.\""},{"time":63000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":66000,"text":"But I want to tell you something useful -- and here it is, so concentrate now."},{"time":71000,"text":"This evening, there's a reception in the University's Museum of Natural History."},{"time":74000,"text":"And it's a wonderful setting, as I hope you'll find,"},{"time":76000,"text":"and a great icon to the best of the Victorian tradition."},{"time":81000,"text":"It's very unlikely -- in this special setting, and this collection of people --"},{"time":86000,"text":"but you might just find yourself talking to someone you'd rather wish that you weren't."},{"time":89000,"text":"So here's what you do."},{"time":91000,"text":"When they say to you, \"What do you do?\" -- you say, \"I'm a statistician.\""},{"time":95000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":96000,"text":"Well, except they've been pre-warned now, and they'll know you're making it up."},{"time":100000,"text":"And then one of two things will happen."},{"time":102000,"text":"They'll either discover their long-lost cousin in the other corner of the room"},{"time":104000,"text":"and run over and talk to them."},{"time":106000,"text":"Or they'll suddenly become parched and/or hungry -- and often both --"},{"time":109000,"text":"and sprint off for a drink and some food."},{"time":111000,"text":"And you'll be left in peace to talk to the person you really want to talk to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115000,"text":"It's one of the challenges in our profession to try and explain what we do."},{"time":118000,"text":"We're not top on people's lists for dinner party guests and conversations and so on."},{"time":123000,"text":"And it's something I've never really found a good way of doing."},{"time":125000,"text":"But my wife -- who was then my girlfriend --"},{"time":128000,"text":"managed it much better than I've ever been able to."},{"time":131000,"text":"Many years ago, when we first started going out, she was working for the BBC in Britain,"},{"time":134000,"text":"and I was, at that stage, working in America."},{"time":136000,"text":"I was coming back to visit her."},{"time":138000,"text":"She told this to one of her colleagues, who said, \"Well, what does your boyfriend do?\""},{"time":144000,"text":"Sarah thought quite hard about the things I'd explained --"},{"time":146000,"text":"and she concentrated, in those days, on listening."},{"time":150000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":153000,"text":"Don't tell her I said that."},{"time":155000,"text":"And she was thinking about the work I did developing mathematical models"},{"time":159000,"text":"for understanding evolution and modern genetics."},{"time":162000,"text":"So when her colleague said, \"What does he do?\""},{"time":165000,"text":"She paused and said, \"He models things.\""},{"time":169000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":170000,"text":"Well, her colleague suddenly got much more interested than I had any right to expect"},{"time":174000,"text":"and went on and said, \"What does he model?\""},{"time":177000,"text":"Well, Sarah thought a little bit more about my work and said, \"Genes.\""},{"time":180000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":184000,"text":"\"He models genes.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":186000,"text":"That is my first love, and that's what I'll tell you a little bit about."},{"time":190000,"text":"What I want to do more generally is to get you thinking about"},{"time":194000,"text":"the place of uncertainty and randomness and chance in our world,"},{"time":197000,"text":"and how we react to that, and how well we do or don't think about it."},{"time":202000,"text":"So you've had a pretty easy time up till now --"},{"time":204000,"text":"a few laughs, and all that kind of thing -- in the talks to date."},{"time":206000,"text":"You've got to think, and I'm going to ask you some questions."},{"time":209000,"text":"So here's the scene for the first question I'm going to ask you."},{"time":211000,"text":"Can you imagine tossing a coin successively?"},{"time":214000,"text":"And for some reason -- which shall remain rather vague --"},{"time":217000,"text":"we're interested in a particular pattern."},{"time":219000,"text":"Here's one -- a head, followed by a tail, followed by a tail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222000,"text":"So suppose we toss a coin repeatedly."},{"time":225000,"text":"Then the pattern, head-tail-tail, that we've suddenly become fixated with happens here."},{"time":230000,"text":"And you can count: one, two, three, four, five, six, seven, eight, nine, 10 --"},{"time":234000,"text":"it happens after the 10th toss."},{"time":236000,"text":"So you might think there are more interesting things to do, but humor me for the moment."},{"time":239000,"text":"Imagine this half of the audience each get out coins, and they toss them"},{"time":243000,"text":"until they first see the pattern head-tail-tail."},{"time":246000,"text":"The first time they do it, maybe it happens after the 10th toss, as here."},{"time":248000,"text":"The second time, maybe it's after the fourth toss."},{"time":250000,"text":"The next time, after the 15th toss."},{"time":252000,"text":"So you do that lots and lots of times, and you average those numbers."},{"time":255000,"text":"That's what I want this side to think about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258000,"text":"The other half of the audience doesn't like head-tail-tail --"},{"time":260000,"text":"they think, for deep cultural reasons, that's boring --"},{"time":263000,"text":"and they're much more interested in a different pattern -- head-tail-head."},{"time":266000,"text":"So, on this side, you get out your coins, and you toss and toss and toss."},{"time":269000,"text":"And you count the number of times until the pattern head-tail-head appears"},{"time":272000,"text":"and you average them. OK?"},{"time":275000,"text":"So on this side, you've got a number --"},{"time":277000,"text":"you've done it lots of times, so you get it accurately --"},{"time":279000,"text":"which is the average number of tosses until head-tail-tail."},{"time":282000,"text":"On this side, you've got a number -- the average number of tosses until head-tail-head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286000,"text":"So here's a deep mathematical fact --"},{"time":288000,"text":"if you've got two numbers, one of three things must be true."},{"time":291000,"text":"Either they're the same, or this one's bigger than this one,"},{"time":294000,"text":"or this one's bigger than that one."},{"time":295000,"text":"So what's going on here?"},{"time":298000,"text":"So you've all got to think about this, and you've all got to vote --"},{"time":300000,"text":"and we're not moving on."},{"time":301000,"text":"And I don't want to end up in the two-minute silence"},{"time":303000,"text":"to give you more time to think about it, until everyone's expressed a view. OK."},{"time":307000,"text":"So what you want to do is compare the average number of tosses until we first see"},{"time":311000,"text":"head-tail-head with the average number of tosses until we first see head-tail-tail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316000,"text":"Who thinks that A is true --"},{"time":318000,"text":"that, on average, it'll take longer to see head-tail-head than head-tail-tail?"},{"time":322000,"text":"Who thinks that B is true -- that on average, they're the same?"},{"time":326000,"text":"Who thinks that C is true -- that, on average, it'll take less time"},{"time":328000,"text":"to see head-tail-head than head-tail-tail?"},{"time":332000,"text":"OK, who hasn't voted yet? Because that's really naughty -- I said you had to."},{"time":335000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":337000,"text":"OK. So most people think B is true."},{"time":340000,"text":"And you might be relieved to know even rather distinguished mathematicians think that."},{"time":343000,"text":"It's not. A is true here."},{"time":347000,"text":"It takes longer, on average."},{"time":349000,"text":"In fact, the average number of tosses till head-tail-head is 10"},{"time":351000,"text":"and the average number of tosses until head-tail-tail is eight."},{"time":356000,"text":"How could that be?"},{"time":359000,"text":"Anything different about the two patterns?"},{"time":365000,"text":"There is. Head-tail-head overlaps itself."},{"time":370000,"text":"If you went head-tail-head-tail-head, you can cunningly get two occurrences"},{"time":374000,"text":"of the pattern in only five tosses."},{"time":377000,"text":"You can't do that with head-tail-tail."},{"time":379000,"text":"That turns out to be important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381000,"text":"There are two ways of thinking about this."},{"time":383000,"text":"I'll give you one of them."},{"time":385000,"text":"So imagine -- let's suppose we're doing it."},{"time":387000,"text":"On this side -- remember, you're excited about head-tail-tail;"},{"time":389000,"text":"you're excited about head-tail-head."},{"time":391000,"text":"We start tossing a coin, and we get a head --"},{"time":394000,"text":"and you start sitting on the edge of your seat"},{"time":395000,"text":"because something great and wonderful, or awesome, might be about to happen."},{"time":400000,"text":"The next toss is a tail -- you get really excited."},{"time":402000,"text":"The champagne's on ice just next to you; you've got the glasses chilled to celebrate."},{"time":406000,"text":"You're waiting with bated breath for the final toss."},{"time":408000,"text":"And if it comes down a head, that's great."},{"time":410000,"text":"You're done, and you celebrate."},{"time":412000,"text":"If it's a tail -- well, rather disappointedly, you put the glasses away"},{"time":414000,"text":"and put the champagne back."},{"time":416000,"text":"And you keep tossing, to wait for the next head, to get excited."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420000,"text":"On this side, there's a different experience."},{"time":422000,"text":"It's the same for the first two parts of the sequence."},{"time":425000,"text":"You're a little bit excited with the first head --"},{"time":427000,"text":"you get rather more excited with the next tail."},{"time":429000,"text":"Then you toss the coin."},{"time":431000,"text":"If it's a tail, you crack open the champagne."},{"time":434000,"text":"If it's a head you're disappointed,"},{"time":436000,"text":"but you're still a third of the way to your pattern again."},{"time":439000,"text":"And that's an informal way of presenting it -- that's why there's a difference."},{"time":443000,"text":"Another way of thinking about it --"},{"time":445000,"text":"if we tossed a coin eight million times,"},{"time":447000,"text":"then we'd expect a million head-tail-heads"},{"time":449000,"text":"and a million head-tail-tails -- but the head-tail-heads could occur in clumps."},{"time":456000,"text":"So if you want to put a million things down amongst eight million positions"},{"time":458000,"text":"and you can have some of them overlapping, the clumps will be further apart."},{"time":463000,"text":"It's another way of getting the intuition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465000,"text":"What's the point I want to make?"},{"time":467000,"text":"It's a very, very simple example, an easily stated question in probability,"},{"time":471000,"text":"which every -- you're in good company -- everybody gets wrong."},{"time":474000,"text":"This is my little diversion into my real passion, which is genetics."},{"time":478000,"text":"There's a connection between head-tail-heads and head-tail-tails in genetics,"},{"time":481000,"text":"and it's the following."},{"time":484000,"text":"When you toss a coin, you get a sequence of heads and tails."},{"time":487000,"text":"When you look at DNA, there's a sequence of not two things -- heads and tails --"},{"time":490000,"text":"but four letters -- As, Gs, Cs and Ts."},{"time":493000,"text":"And there are little chemical scissors, called restriction enzymes"},{"time":496000,"text":"which cut DNA whenever they see particular patterns."},{"time":498000,"text":"And they're an enormously useful tool in modern molecular biology."},{"time":503000,"text":"And instead of asking the question, \"How long until I see a head-tail-head?\" --"},{"time":506000,"text":"you can ask, \"How big will the chunks be when I use a restriction enzyme"},{"time":509000,"text":"which cuts whenever it sees G-A-A-G, for example?"},{"time":513000,"text":"How long will those chunks be?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":515000,"text":"That's a rather trivial connection between probability and genetics."},{"time":520000,"text":"There's a much deeper connection, which I don't have time to go into"},{"time":523000,"text":"and that is that modern genetics is a really exciting area of science."},{"time":526000,"text":"And we'll hear some talks later in the conference specifically about that."},{"time":530000,"text":"But it turns out that unlocking the secrets in the information generated by modern"},{"time":534000,"text":"experimental technologies, a key part of that has to do with fairly sophisticated --"},{"time":539000,"text":"you'll be relieved to know that I do something useful in my day job,"},{"time":542000,"text":"rather more sophisticated than the head-tail-head story --"},{"time":544000,"text":"but quite sophisticated computer modelings and mathematical modelings"},{"time":548000,"text":"and modern statistical techniques."},{"time":550000,"text":"And I will give you two little snippets -- two examples --"},{"time":553000,"text":"of projects we're involved in in my group in Oxford,"},{"time":556000,"text":"both of which I think are rather exciting."},{"time":558000,"text":"You know about the Human Genome Project."},{"time":560000,"text":"That was a project which aimed to read one copy of the human genome."},{"time":566000,"text":"The natural thing to do after you've done that --"},{"time":568000,"text":"and that's what this project, the International HapMap Project,"},{"time":570000,"text":"which is a collaboration between labs in five or six different countries."},{"time":575000,"text":"Think of the Human Genome Project as learning what we've got in common,"},{"time":579000,"text":"and the HapMap Project is trying to understand"},{"time":581000,"text":"where there are differences between different people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583000,"text":"Why do we care about that?"},{"time":585000,"text":"Well, there are lots of reasons."},{"time":587000,"text":"The most pressing one is that we want to understand how some differences"},{"time":591000,"text":"make some people susceptible to one disease -- type-2 diabetes, for example --"},{"time":595000,"text":"and other differences make people more susceptible to heart disease,"},{"time":600000,"text":"or stroke, or autism and so on."},{"time":602000,"text":"That's one big project."},{"time":604000,"text":"There's a second big project,"},{"time":606000,"text":"recently funded by the Wellcome Trust in this country,"},{"time":608000,"text":"involving very large studies --"},{"time":610000,"text":"thousands of individuals, with each of eight different diseases,"},{"time":613000,"text":"common diseases like type-1 and type-2 diabetes, and coronary heart disease,"},{"time":617000,"text":"bipolar disease and so on -- to try and understand the genetics."},{"time":621000,"text":"To try and understand what it is about genetic differences that causes the diseases."},{"time":624000,"text":"Why do we want to do that?"},{"time":626000,"text":"Because we understand very little about most human diseases."},{"time":629000,"text":"We don't know what causes them."},{"time":631000,"text":"And if we can get in at the bottom and understand the genetics,"},{"time":633000,"text":"we'll have a window on the way the disease works,"},{"time":636000,"text":"and a whole new way about thinking about disease therapies"},{"time":638000,"text":"and preventative treatment and so on."},{"time":641000,"text":"So that's, as I said, the little diversion on my main love."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644000,"text":"Back to some of the more mundane issues of thinking about uncertainty."},{"time":649000,"text":"Here's another quiz for you --"},{"time":651000,"text":"now suppose we've got a test for a disease"},{"time":653000,"text":"which isn't infallible, but it's pretty good."},{"time":655000,"text":"It gets it right 99 percent of the time."},{"time":658000,"text":"And I take one of you, or I take someone off the street,"},{"time":661000,"text":"and I test them for the disease in question."},{"time":663000,"text":"Let's suppose there's a test for HIV -- the virus that causes AIDS --"},{"time":667000,"text":"and the test says the person has the disease."},{"time":670000,"text":"What's the chance that they do?"},{"time":673000,"text":"The test gets it right 99 percent of the time."},{"time":675000,"text":"So a natural answer is 99 percent."},{"time":679000,"text":"Who likes that answer?"},{"time":681000,"text":"Come on -- everyone's got to get involved."},{"time":682000,"text":"Don't think you don't trust me anymore."},{"time":684000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":685000,"text":"Well, you're right to be a bit skeptical, because that's not the answer."},{"time":688000,"text":"That's what you might think."},{"time":690000,"text":"It's not the answer, and it's not because it's only part of the story."},{"time":693000,"text":"It actually depends on how common or how rare the disease is."},{"time":696000,"text":"So let me try and illustrate that."},{"time":698000,"text":"Here's a little caricature of a million individuals."},{"time":702000,"text":"So let's think about a disease that affects --"},{"time":705000,"text":"it's pretty rare, it affects one person in 10,000."},{"time":707000,"text":"Amongst these million individuals, most of them are healthy"},{"time":710000,"text":"and some of them will have the disease."},{"time":712000,"text":"And in fact, if this is the prevalence of the disease,"},{"time":715000,"text":"about 100 will have the disease and the rest won't."},{"time":718000,"text":"So now suppose we test them all."},{"time":720000,"text":"What happens?"},{"time":722000,"text":"Well, amongst the 100 who do have the disease,"},{"time":724000,"text":"the test will get it right 99 percent of the time, and 99 will test positive."},{"time":729000,"text":"Amongst all these other people who don't have the disease,"},{"time":731000,"text":"the test will get it right 99 percent of the time."},{"time":734000,"text":"It'll only get it wrong one percent of the time."},{"time":736000,"text":"But there are so many of them that there'll be an enormous number of false positives."},{"time":740000,"text":"Put that another way --"},{"time":742000,"text":"of all of them who test positive -- so here they are, the individuals involved --"},{"time":747000,"text":"less than one in 100 actually have the disease."},{"time":752000,"text":"So even though we think the test is accurate, the important part of the story is"},{"time":756000,"text":"there's another bit of information we need."}]},{"cues":[{"time":759000,"text":"Here's the key intuition."},{"time":762000,"text":"What we have to do, once we know the test is positive,"},{"time":765000,"text":"is to weigh up the plausibility, or the likelihood, of two competing explanations."},{"time":771000,"text":"Each of those explanations has a likely bit and an unlikely bit."},{"time":774000,"text":"One explanation is that the person doesn't have the disease --"},{"time":777000,"text":"that's overwhelmingly likely, if you pick someone at random --"},{"time":780000,"text":"but the test gets it wrong, which is unlikely."},{"time":784000,"text":"The other explanation is that the person does have the disease -- that's unlikely --"},{"time":787000,"text":"but the test gets it right, which is likely."},{"time":790000,"text":"And the number we end up with --"},{"time":792000,"text":"that number which is a little bit less than one in 100 --"},{"time":795000,"text":"is to do with how likely one of those explanations is relative to the other."},{"time":801000,"text":"Each of them taken together is unlikely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804000,"text":"Here's a more topical example of exactly the same thing."},{"time":807000,"text":"Those of you in Britain will know about what's become rather a celebrated case"},{"time":811000,"text":"of a woman called Sally Clark, who had two babies who died suddenly."},{"time":816000,"text":"And initially, it was thought that they died of what's known informally as \"cot death,\""},{"time":820000,"text":"and more formally as \"Sudden Infant Death Syndrome.\""},{"time":823000,"text":"For various reasons, she was later charged with murder."},{"time":825000,"text":"And at the trial, her trial, a very distinguished pediatrician gave evidence"},{"time":829000,"text":"that the chance of two cot deaths, innocent deaths, in a family like hers --"},{"time":834000,"text":"which was professional and non-smoking -- was one in 73 million."},{"time":841000,"text":"To cut a long story short, she was convicted at the time."},{"time":844000,"text":"Later, and fairly recently, acquitted on appeal -- in fact, on the second appeal."},{"time":849000,"text":"And just to set it in context, you can imagine how awful it is for someone"},{"time":853000,"text":"to have lost one child, and then two, if they're innocent,"},{"time":856000,"text":"to be convicted of murdering them."},{"time":858000,"text":"To be put through the stress of the trial, convicted of murdering them --"},{"time":860000,"text":"and to spend time in a women's prison, where all the other prisoners"},{"time":863000,"text":"think you killed your children -- is a really awful thing to happen to someone."},{"time":868000,"text":"And it happened in large part here because the expert got the statistics"},{"time":873000,"text":"horribly wrong, in two different ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":876000,"text":"So where did he get the one in 73 million number?"},{"time":880000,"text":"He looked at some research, which said the chance of one cot death in a family"},{"time":883000,"text":"like Sally Clark's is about one in 8,500."},{"time":888000,"text":"So he said, \"I'll assume that if you have one cot death in a family,"},{"time":892000,"text":"the chance of a second child dying from cot death aren't changed.\""},{"time":896000,"text":"So that's what statisticians would call an assumption of independence."},{"time":899000,"text":"It's like saying, \"If you toss a coin and get a head the first time,"},{"time":901000,"text":"that won't affect the chance of getting a head the second time.\""},{"time":904000,"text":"So if you toss a coin twice, the chance of getting a head twice are a half --"},{"time":909000,"text":"that's the chance the first time -- times a half -- the chance a second time."},{"time":912000,"text":"So he said, \"Here,"},{"time":914000,"text":"I'll assume that these events are independent."},{"time":918000,"text":"When you multiply 8,500 together twice,"},{"time":920000,"text":"you get about 73 million.\""},{"time":922000,"text":"And none of this was stated to the court as an assumption"},{"time":924000,"text":"or presented to the jury that way."},{"time":927000,"text":"Unfortunately here -- and, really, regrettably --"},{"time":930000,"text":"first of all, in a situation like this you'd have to verify it empirically."},{"time":934000,"text":"And secondly, it's palpably false."},{"time":937000,"text":"There are lots and lots of things that we don't know about sudden infant deaths."},{"time":942000,"text":"It might well be that there are environmental factors that we're not aware of,"},{"time":945000,"text":"and it's pretty likely to be the case that there are"},{"time":947000,"text":"genetic factors we're not aware of."},{"time":949000,"text":"So if a family suffers from one cot death, you'd put them in a high-risk group."},{"time":952000,"text":"They've probably got these environmental risk factors"},{"time":954000,"text":"and/or genetic risk factors we don't know about."},{"time":957000,"text":"And to argue, then, that the chance of a second death is as if you didn't know"},{"time":960000,"text":"that information is really silly."},{"time":963000,"text":"It's worse than silly -- it's really bad science."},{"time":967000,"text":"Nonetheless, that's how it was presented, and at trial nobody even argued it."},{"time":972000,"text":"That's the first problem."},{"time":974000,"text":"The second problem is, what does the number of one in 73 million mean?"},{"time":978000,"text":"So after Sally Clark was convicted --"},{"time":980000,"text":"you can imagine, it made rather a splash in the press --"},{"time":984000,"text":"one of the journalists from one of Britain's more reputable newspapers wrote that"},{"time":991000,"text":"what the expert had said was,"},{"time":993000,"text":"\"The chance that she was innocent was one in 73 million.\""},{"time":998000,"text":"Now, that's a logical error."},{"time":1000000,"text":"It's exactly the same logical error as the logical error of thinking that"},{"time":1003000,"text":"after the disease test, which is 99 percent accurate,"},{"time":1005000,"text":"the chance of having the disease is 99 percent."},{"time":1009000,"text":"In the disease example, we had to bear in mind two things,"},{"time":1013000,"text":"one of which was the possibility that the test got it right or not."},{"time":1017000,"text":"And the other one was the chance, a priori, that the person had the disease or not."},{"time":1021000,"text":"It's exactly the same in this context."},{"time":1024000,"text":"There are two things involved -- two parts to the explanation."},{"time":1028000,"text":"We want to know how likely, or relatively how likely, two different explanations are."},{"time":1032000,"text":"One of them is that Sally Clark was innocent --"},{"time":1035000,"text":"which is, a priori, overwhelmingly likely --"},{"time":1037000,"text":"most mothers don't kill their children."},{"time":1040000,"text":"And the second part of the explanation"},{"time":1042000,"text":"is that she suffered an incredibly unlikely event."},{"time":1045000,"text":"Not as unlikely as one in 73 million, but nonetheless rather unlikely."},{"time":1049000,"text":"The other explanation is that she was guilty."},{"time":1051000,"text":"Now, we probably think a priori that's unlikely."},{"time":1053000,"text":"And we certainly should think in the context of a criminal trial"},{"time":1056000,"text":"that that's unlikely, because of the presumption of innocence."},{"time":1059000,"text":"And then if she were trying to kill the children, she succeeded."},{"time":1063000,"text":"So the chance that she's innocent isn't one in 73 million."},{"time":1067000,"text":"We don't know what it is."},{"time":1069000,"text":"It has to do with weighing up the strength of the other evidence against her"},{"time":1073000,"text":"and the statistical evidence."},{"time":1075000,"text":"We know the children died."},{"time":1077000,"text":"What matters is how likely or unlikely, relative to each other,"},{"time":1081000,"text":"the two explanations are."},{"time":1083000,"text":"And they're both implausible."},{"time":1086000,"text":"There's a situation where errors in statistics had really profound"},{"time":1090000,"text":"and really unfortunate consequences."},{"time":1093000,"text":"In fact, there are two other women who were convicted on the basis of the"},{"time":1095000,"text":"evidence of this pediatrician, who have subsequently been released on appeal."},{"time":1099000,"text":"Many cases were reviewed."},{"time":1101000,"text":"And it's particularly topical because he's currently facing a disrepute charge"},{"time":1105000,"text":"at Britain's General Medical Council."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1108000,"text":"So just to conclude -- what are the take-home messages from this?"},{"time":1112000,"text":"Well, we know that randomness and uncertainty and chance"},{"time":1116000,"text":"are very much a part of our everyday life."},{"time":1119000,"text":"It's also true -- and, although, you, as a collective, are very special in many ways,"},{"time":1124000,"text":"you're completely typical in not getting the examples I gave right."},{"time":1128000,"text":"It's very well documented that people get things wrong."},{"time":1131000,"text":"They make errors of logic in reasoning with uncertainty."},{"time":1135000,"text":"We can cope with the subtleties of language brilliantly --"},{"time":1137000,"text":"and there are interesting evolutionary questions about how we got here."},{"time":1140000,"text":"We are not good at reasoning with uncertainty."},{"time":1143000,"text":"That's an issue in our everyday lives."},{"time":1145000,"text":"As you've heard from many of the talks, statistics underpins an enormous amount"},{"time":1148000,"text":"of research in science -- in social science, in medicine"},{"time":1151000,"text":"and indeed, quite a lot of industry."},{"time":1153000,"text":"All of quality control, which has had a major impact on industrial processing,"},{"time":1157000,"text":"is underpinned by statistics."},{"time":1159000,"text":"It's something we're bad at doing."},{"time":1161000,"text":"At the very least, we should recognize that, and we tend not to."},{"time":1164000,"text":"To go back to the legal context, at the Sally Clark trial"},{"time":1168000,"text":"all of the lawyers just accepted what the expert said."},{"time":1172000,"text":"So if a pediatrician had come out and said to a jury,"},{"time":1174000,"text":"\"I know how to build bridges. I've built one down the road."},{"time":1177000,"text":"Please drive your car home over it,\""},{"time":1179000,"text":"they would have said, \"Well, pediatricians don't know how to build bridges."},{"time":1181000,"text":"That's what engineers do.\""},{"time":1183000,"text":"On the other hand, he came out and effectively said, or implied,"},{"time":1186000,"text":"\"I know how to reason with uncertainty. I know how to do statistics.\""},{"time":1189000,"text":"And everyone said, \"Well, that's fine. He's an expert.\""},{"time":1192000,"text":"So we need to understand where our competence is and isn't."},{"time":1195000,"text":"Exactly the same kinds of issues arose in the early days of DNA profiling,"},{"time":1199000,"text":"when scientists, and lawyers and in some cases judges,"},{"time":1203000,"text":"routinely misrepresented evidence."},{"time":1207000,"text":"Usually -- one hopes -- innocently, but misrepresented evidence."},{"time":1210000,"text":"Forensic scientists said, \"The chance that this guy's innocent is one in three million.\""},{"time":1215000,"text":"Even if you believe the number, just like the 73 million to one,"},{"time":1217000,"text":"that's not what it meant."},{"time":1219000,"text":"And there have been celebrated appeal cases"},{"time":1221000,"text":"in Britain and elsewhere because of that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1223000,"text":"And just to finish in the context of the legal system."},{"time":1226000,"text":"It's all very well to say, \"Let's do our best to present the evidence.\""},{"time":1230000,"text":"But more and more, in cases of DNA profiling -- this is another one --"},{"time":1233000,"text":"we expect juries, who are ordinary people --"},{"time":1236000,"text":"and it's documented they're very bad at this --"},{"time":1238000,"text":"we expect juries to be able to cope with the sorts of reasoning that goes on."},{"time":1242000,"text":"In other spheres of life, if people argued -- well, except possibly for politics --"},{"time":1247000,"text":"but in other spheres of life, if people argued illogically,"},{"time":1249000,"text":"we'd say that's not a good thing."},{"time":1251000,"text":"We sort of expect it of politicians and don't hope for much more."},{"time":1255000,"text":"In the case of uncertainty, we get it wrong all the time --"},{"time":1258000,"text":"and at the very least, we should be aware of that,"},{"time":1260000,"text":"and ideally, we might try and do something about it."},{"time":1262000,"text":"Thanks very much."}]}]}